# ADFixErrors — Changelog

> v1.0 – v1.14 by Magno Borgo. v1.15 and later by Antoine Danion.

## [2.1.1] — 2026-02-25
- Added a clean logger for better output in the console and easier debugging.

## [2.1.0] — 2025-09-15
- Optimized the search by stopping early when all files have been found.
- Fixed the search traversing system folders such as `RECYCLE.BIN`.
- Result messages now show at most 30 nodes followed by "and more…" to avoid overwhelming output.
- Improved console output to surface relevant information more clearly.

## [2.0.0] — 2025-09-14
- Added a selective search panel allowing users to include or exclude specific node types from the scan.
- Added progress bars throughout long-running operations with cancellation support.
- Extracted font fixing into its own dedicated `fix_fonts_errors()` function.
- Bypassed Nuke Non-Commercial 10-node memory limitation using TCL.
- Major refactor for readability and maintainability.

## [1.16] — 2025-09-14
- Refactored for improved readability and maintainability.
- Switched from `fnmatch` to `re` for more precise frame pattern matching (fixes incorrect matches with `%0Xd` patterns).

## [1.15] — 2025-09-12
- Improved handling of file extensions with fewer or more than 3 characters (fixes `.cube` file issues).

## [1.14] — 2014-04-01
_(Magno Borgo)_
- Fixed a font path issue that halted the script on Nuke v8.
- Fixed handling of multiple Read nodes sharing the same file reference.

## [1.13] — 2013-07-25
_(Magno Borgo)_
- Reverted check order to avoid prompting for a search directory when no errors are present.

## [1.12] — 2013-02-07
_(Magno Borgo)_
- Added `vfield_file` to the searched knob types.
- Automatic fix for incorrect font paths on Text nodes.

## [1.0] — 2012-11-23
_(Magno Borgo)_
- Initial release.
- Searches all nodes with a `file` property.
- Single `os.walk` pass for faster searches.
- Generalized `%0d` frame pattern handling.
- Progress task with cancellation support.
